Colombian Stocks: Cementos Argos, Interbolsa, Mineros Rise

-- B y   C a m i l a   R u s s o
-- 
2011-02-25T22:41:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-25/colombian-stocks-cementos-argos-interbolsa-mineros-rise.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index increased 1.2 percent to 14,746.12, while
the Colcap Index gained 0.8 percent to 1,713.40.    Cementos Argos SA  (CEMARGOS CB), Colombia’s biggest cement
maker, rose 2.1 percent to 10,720 pesos.  Grupo de Inversiones
Suramericana SA , Cementos Argos’s parent company, said 2010
income rose 56 percent from a year earlier to 696.3 billion
pesos ($367 million).  Interbolsa SA (INTBOL CB) climbed 0.7 percent to 2,800
pesos. The parent company of Colombia’s biggest brokerage said
2010 income was 40.8 billion pesos, according to a regulatory
filing. The company didn’t provide 2009 results.    Mineros SA  (MINEROS CB), Colombia’s largest gold-mining
company, jumped 3.7 percent to 6,740 pesos. Hedge-fund managers
and other large speculators increased their net-long position in
New York gold futures in the week ended Feb. 22, according to
U.S. Commodity Futures Trading Commission data.  Oil producers rose as crude capped its biggest weekly gain
in two years on concern the turmoil that has cut Libya’s output
may spread to other parts of the Middle East.    Canacol Energy Ltd . (CNEC CB), the Calgary-based oil
company, climbed 1.6 percent to 3,115 pesos, the highest level
since Nov. 24.    Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp . (PREC CB), the Toronto-based
oil producer that operates fields in Colombia, increased 2.8
percent to 62,200 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Camila Russo in New York at 
